sentences: Saif Musaad (born 30 January 1997), professionally known as Safe (stylized as SAFE), is a singer, rapper, and songwriter from Toronto, Ontario.
Saif Musaad was born on 30 January 1997 in Abu Dhabi, United Arab Emirates and is of Eritrean descent.
In 2015 he began uploading songs to SoundCloud, and "Feel" became a hit, receiving 4.15 million plays over four years.

In 2017 he moved to New York, from where he continued to release singles including "No Diamonds," which criticized the ostentatious display of the trappings of wealth, and premiered at Vice on 24 September 2018, and "New Regime," whose accompanying video depicted the seamy side of his hometown and his reasons for leaving.

In 2018, he was deeply affected by the murder of his close friend Smoke Dawg.

During the same period, Safe's vocals were featured on a number of other artists' tracks, including the September 2018 single "Listen Closely" from fellow Canadians DVBBS, the track "Don't Pretend" from Khalid's 2019 album Free Spirit, and YG's track "Play Too Much" on his 2019 album 4Real 4Real.
In May 2019, Safe released his debut studio album Stay, on RCA Records.
